value: Breeds in southeastern Europe and southwestern Asia from Kiev, Kharkov, Ryazan, Simbirsk, Orenburg, Turgai, Semipalatinsk and the southern Altai, south to the mouth of the Danube, Astrakan, Aral-Caspian Province and Zaissan. Migrates south through western and central Africa to Cape Province.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Palearctic winter visitor, open high altitude grassland or mudflats: NE Namibia, Botswana, central South Africa; scattered irregularly in West Africa.
Romania to sw Russia and n Kazakhstan; winters to S Africa
open barren areas, sparse grass, cleared ground, sandy beaches
